{"type":"step-attempt","step":"spec-review","sessionId":"ffa0e409-bf26-4c4e-a179-08c3d953d219","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/orphan-worktree-doctor/spec-review-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/orphan-worktree-doctor/tasks.md","title":"`git worktree prune` runs unconditionally including during dry-run","rationale":"T-03 step 2 calls `worktreeManager.prune(repoRoot)` before checking the `force` flag. This silently mutates git state (clears stale worktree refs) even in dry-run mode, violating the 'dry-run = no mutations' contract users expect. The operation is low-risk (no data loss), but the inconsistency is a UX defect. Fix: guard the call with `if (force)`."},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/orphan-worktree-doctor/tasks.md","title":"`PRUNE_USAGE` help string content left undefined","rationale":"T-04 instructs adding a `PRUNE_USAGE` constant but does not specify its content. Implementers must invent the help text without a canonical reference, risking inconsistent style. Fix: add an example string to T-04, mirroring the format of existing usage constants such as `CANCEL_USAGE`."}],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"specrunner/changes/orphan-worktree-doctor/design.md","title":"Detection correctness verified against source","rationale":"`JobStateStore.list` skips the `canceled/` directory (not scanned even with `includeArchived: true`), so partially-canceled jobs whose worktrees survived are correctly classified as orphans. The `${getJobSlug(state)}-${state.jobId.slice(0,8)}` protected-set key reproduces the exact directory name from `buildWorktreePath` because `loadSplitLayout` injects `request.slug` from the slug-directory name at load time."},{"severity":"low","file":"specrunner/changes/orphan-worktree-doctor/design.md","title":"Security: no shell injection surface","rationale":"All git invocations use `spawnCommand` (argv array, not shell-interpolated). Branch names and worktree paths from `git worktree list --porcelain` are passed as discrete argv elements, so no shell injection is possible from crafted git output."}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-06-29T03:54:44.546Z","endedAt":"2026-06-29T03:58:21.164Z"}
