{"type":"step-attempt","step":"code-review","sessionId":"fcf6ddf8-b122-49c4-b3d7-ba30ca3adddc","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/orphan-worktree-doctor/review-feedback-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[{"severity":"medium","resolution":"fixable","file":"src/core/prune/runner.ts","title":"`removed` counter increments and `info` says \"Removed:\" even when `worktreeManager.remove` throws","rationale":"When `worktreeManager.remove` throws, a warning is appended but execution continues unconditionally to `info.push(\"Removed: /path ...\")` and `removed++`. The final message \"Removed N orphan worktree(s)\" then contradicts the warning \"failed to remove worktree\". The test for this path only asserts `exitCode` and `warnings`, not `info` or `message`, so the misleading output is uncaught.","line":177},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"tests/unit/core/prune/runner.test.ts","title":"Test `\"continues with warning when worktreeManager.prune fails\"` never actually calls `worktreeManager.prune`","rationale":"The test sets `mockScan.mockResolvedValue([])`, causing `pruneOrphanWorktrees` to return early before `worktreeManager.prune` is called. The test comment even acknowledges this (\"No orphans → early return before prune is called\"). The graceful-handling path for prune failure when orphans exist is untested.","line":276}],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"specrunner/changes/orphan-worktree-doctor/test-cases.md","title":"TC-013 specifies \"without invoking git worktree list\" but implementation always calls git","rationale":"TC-013 states the implementation should return [] without calling `git worktree list` when the base dir is absent. The implementation always calls git and filters results (design.md D2 aligns with this). Behavior is correct; the test case spec has an over-constraint that doesn't match the design."},{"severity":"low","file":"tests/unit/core/doctor/orphan-worktrees-check.test.ts","title":"TC-001/TC-007 classified as `integration` but implemented as unit tests with mocks","rationale":"T-02 acceptance criteria called for a \"real temp git repo\" fixture test. The actual tests use mocked spawn and listStates. All `must` AC items are functionally satisfied at the mock level; no real git operations are integration-tested for these scenarios."}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-06-29T04:14:50.641Z","endedAt":"2026-06-29T04:21:01.673Z"}
{"type":"lineage","step":"code-review","ts":"2026-06-29T04:21:01.673Z","outputs":[{"path":"specrunner/changes/orphan-worktree-doctor/review-feedback-002.md","hash":null}],"inputs":[{"path":"specrunner/changes/orphan-worktree-doctor/design.md","hash":"sha256:f8c5ca3b711130487f5a04bda25b2ac3d18a00120bd218caf76e6bdd292eb94a"},{"path":"specrunner/changes/orphan-worktree-doctor/tasks.md","hash":"sha256:aa75a70beb40d5014430f264a02dff1fb49b6f705b85cc0b51e6ef8086be5915"},{"path":"specrunner/changes/orphan-worktree-doctor/test-cases.md","hash":"sha256:27c02235787c3832c8e8c54b2923d6c7f2295992244704bd6c1b62f190deeffa","required":false},{"path":".","hash":null}]}
